<plot>Fine Threads is a documentary by teenage women from Queens, NY, exploring notions of beauty, immigrant ideals, and religion. They weave a narrative out of intimate exchanges in an unlikely place: the Indian threading salon. Told through interviews, and verite, the young women assemble a story about coming of age in the city.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?195156</url></doc>
